# B2: Gradual — `any`-typed argument is vacuously satisfying.
# When the argument type is `any`, the constraint is not discharged
# (gradual boundary — no warning).
` { type: "<(a, a) => a -> a -> a" }
lesser(x, y): if(x < y, x, y)
# Call with unannotated (any-typed) argument — no warning expected.
result: lesser(if(1 < 2, 3, 4), 5)
` { type: "number" }
check: result
